condition.narrative: As part of the ESCP: (a) an Environmental and Social Management Framework (ESMF) within 60 days of project effectiveness; (b) aStakeholder Engagement Plan (SEP) within 30 days of Effectiveness (a draft of which has already been developed during preparation);(c) Labor Management Procedures (LMP) within 60 days of Effectiveness; (d) a Resettlement Policy Framework (RPF) within 60 days ofEffectiveness; and (e) an Indigenous Peoples and Afro-Descendants Plan (IPADP) by Effectiveness.

Schedule 2. Section I. A.2. Implementation Arrangement. No later than thirty (30) days after the Effective Date, the Recipient,through SEDECOAS, shall establish, and thereafter operate and maintain, a Project implementation unit (“PIU”) with functions andresources acceptable to the Association, and adequate staff, including: (i) a general coordinator, (ii) a technical coordinator;(iii) a financial management specialist; (iv) a procurement specialist; (v) a monitoring and evaluation specialist; (vi) anenvironmental specialist; (vii) a social development and gender specialist; (viii) a health and safety specialist; and (ix) acommunications specialist; all with functions, qualifications, and responsibilities satisfactory to the Association, as set forthin the Project Operational Manual.

Schedule 2. Section I. C.2. Environmental and Social Standards. Without limitation upon paragraph 1 above, the Recipient, throughSEDECOAS, shall ensure that the Project is implemented in accordance with the Environmental and Social Commitment Plan (“ESCP”), ina manner acceptable to the Association.

Schedule 2. Section I. C.5. Environmental and Social Standards. The Recipient, through SEDECOAS, shall establish, publicize,maintain and operate an accessible grievance mechanism, to receive and facilitate resolution of concerns and grievances ofProject-affected people, and take all measures necessary and appropriate to resolve, or facilitate the resolution of, such concernsand grievances, in a manner acceptable to the Association.

Schedule 2. Section I. C.6. Environmental and Social Standards. The Recipient, through SEDECOAS, shall ensure that all biddingdocuments and contracts for civil works under the Project include the obligation of contractors, subcontractors, and supervisingentities to: (a) comply with the relevant aspects of ESCP and the environmental and social instruments referred to therein; and (b)adopt and enforce codes of conduct that should be provided to and signed by all workers, detailing measures to addressenvironmental, social, health and safety risks, and the risks of sexual exploitation and abuse, sexual harassment and violenceagainst children, all as applicable to such civil works commissioned or carried out pursuant to said contracts.

Schedule 2. Section I. D.1. Inter-Institutional Agreements. To facilitate the carrying out of the Project, and prior to theparticipation of a Project Entity in the implementation of any given Project activity, the Recipient, through SEDECOAS, shall: (a)sign with said Project Entity an Inter-Institutional Agreement with terms and conditions acceptable to the Association; and (b)thereafter maintain said Inter-Institutional Agreement throughout the implementation of the Project.

Schedule 2. Section I. E. Financial Management. No later than one hundred and eighty (180) days after the Effective Date, theRecipient, through SEDECOAS, shall hire and retain, throughout Project implementation, an external, independent, private auditfirm, acceptable to the Association, to provide the audit services described in the Project Operational Manual.
